  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions or legitimate businesses. Key elements typically include:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source of money through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Making the money appear legitimate and accessible\n\nSpecific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but most involve intentionally disguising the origins of criminal proceeds.",
